  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Intern - Marketing & Business Strategy (Keenai Global)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support marketing campaigns across digital channels (social media, content, email, partnerships).</li><li>Conduct customer, market, and competitor research to identify growth opportunities.</li><li>Assist in developing go-to-market strategies for new products or features.</li><li>Analyse user behaviour, campaign performance, and funnel metrics.</li><li>Help shape brand positioning, messaging, and storytelling.</li><li>Work on strategic projects such as partnerships and expansion plans.</li><li>Prepare decks, reports, and insights for internal and investor-facing discussions.</li><li>Perform any other ad-hoc projects as assigned by the team.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Currently pursuing or recently completed a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Business, Marketing, Finance, or a related field.</li><li>Strong interest in wealth management, investing, startups, and fintech.</li><li>Analytical mindset with the ability to connect data to business decisions.</li><li>Comfortable working in fast-paced, startup environments.</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills.</li><li>Proactive, ownership-driven attitude.</li><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to translate data into actionable insights.</li></ul><p><strong>Duration</strong></p><ul><li>Start immediately and commit for at least 3 months. 6 months is highly preferred.</li></ul>",
